Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of
@olive oil{1%tablespoon}, @Sweet and Smoky BBQ Seasoning{1%tablespoon}(half the amount),
@pepper{} and a big pinch of @salt{}. Set aside.

Place @butter{1%tablespoon} in a medium #microwave safe bowl{}; microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, remaining @Sweet and Smoky BBQ Seasoning{}, pepper, and
a big pinch of @salt{}. Add @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/2%cup} and stir until evenly combined.

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Lightly oil a second baking sheet; spread chicken out across sheet. Evenly spread @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}
onto tops of chicken; mound with panko mixture, pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

Roast potatoes on top rack until crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Once potatoes have roasted 5 minutes, add chicken to middle rack and roast until browned and
cooked through, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, cut @Broccoli Florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Place in a large
#microwave-safe bowl{} with @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon}. Cover bowl with #plastic wrap{} and
poke a few holes in wrap. Microwave until broccoli is tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Carefully remove plastic wrap (watch out for steam). Drain any water left in bowl, then toss
broccoli with @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide chicken, potatoes, and broccoli between plates. Drizzle chicken with as much @Mike's Hot Honey{3/4%ounce}
as you like and serve.